---
import BaseLayout from '~/layouts/BaseLayout.astro'
const updated = '2026-06-19'
---

<BaseLayout title="Disclaimer — book·lore" description="What book·lore is and isn't.">
  <section class="spine page">
    <header class="page-head">
      <p class="eyebrow"><a href="/">book·lore</a> / <a href="/legal/">colophon</a> / disclaimer</p>
      <h1>Disclaimer</h1>
      <p class="meta">Last updated: {updated}</p>
    </header>

    <article class="prose">
      <p>
        Everything on book·lore is published in good faith for general information and
        education. Use it at your own risk.
      </p>

      <h2>Summaries are not substitutes</h2>
      <p>
        Entries on book·lore are <em>commentary</em>: opinionated, structured notes that
        map a book. They are not the book itself. If a summary intrigues you, please buy
        the original — the author did the hard work.
      </p>

      <h2>Not financial / medical / legal advice</h2>
      <p>
        Many of the books here touch finance, health, or law. Summaries and analyses are
        <em>about</em> what those books say; they are not professional advice. Consult a
        qualified advisor before acting.
      </p>

      <h2>External links</h2>
      <p>
        We link to third-party sites we find useful (publisher pages, OpenLibrary records).
        We don't control their content; inclusion is not an endorsement.
      </p>

      <h2>Affiliate disclosure</h2>
      <p>
        Some outbound book links may, in the future, be affiliate links. This never affects
        what we summarise or analyse, and any such links will be marked clearly.
      </p>

      <h2>Errors</h2>
      <p>
        Spotted a factual error? Email
        <a href="mailto:whyiswhen@gmail.com">whyiswhen@gmail.com</a> or use the
        <a href="/contact/">contact form</a>. We fix typos and factual mistakes promptly.
      </p>
    </article>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
